race.description: Select & Atlas Events & Party Hire Plate (C1)
race.comment: CRACKEN GOOD TIME (6) remains a maiden but he brings similar form lines to a couple of these and is racing very consistently. He will roll forward and give himself every chance on or near the speed. He looks a great each-way play. GRINZINGER JOY (9) is a last-start maiden winner, defeating EMPRESS OF SOUL (8) who came out and broke her maiden the following start. Both horses are one-paced stayers but they do look well placed here. They are drawn next to each other and it might come down to who gets the better ride. IRLANDAIS (10) is another maiden with strong claims here. He's placed in 10 of his 22 starts. Todd Pannell looks a great booking for him and he can run in the money. DEXTER DREAM (7) is a place chance.
